  <h1>Carrot and Onion Noodles</h1>
  <img src ="carrotonionnoodles.png" height="auto">
  <h2>Recipe</h2>
  <h3>Preparation Time</h3>
  <p>20 minutes</p>
  <h3>Ingredients</h3>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>4 ounces udon noodles</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon canola oil</li>
      <li>1 small onion, thinly sliced</li>
      <li>1 garlic clove, minced</li>
      <li>1/2 cup shredded carrot</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon rice wine vinegar</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <h3>Directions</h3>
  <p>
    <ol>
      <li>Boil udon noodles according to directions.</li>
      <li>Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Add canola oil. </li>
      <li>Add onion; sauté 3 minutes.</li> 
      <li>Add garlic; sauté 30 seconds.</li> 
      <li>Add carrot; sauté 2 mins</li>
      <li>Remove from heat; stir in vinegar, and soy sauce.</li>
      <li>Add noodles; toss to coat. Serve.</li>
    </ol>
  </p>
